==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cruet
<hw>Cru"et</hw> <pr>(kr⟦udd⟧"⟦ecr⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Anglo-French <ets>cruet</ets>, a dim. from OF. <ets>crue</ets>,
<ets>cruie</ets>; of German or Celtic origin, and akin to E.
<ets>crock</ets> an earthen vessel.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A bottle or
vessel; esp., a vial or small glass bottle for holding vinegar, oil,
pepper, or the like, for the table; a caster.</def>
<rj><au>Swift.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>A vessel used to hold wine, oil,
or water for the service of the altar.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>cruet stand</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>cruet-stand</ent>⟦br⟧
